&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;
&lt;i&gt;the triangle of triangles&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Triangular grid graph paper in visualizing and solving problems where three terms add up to some constant value. Angles within a triangle provide an example (the three angles sum to 180 degrees), and so different species of triangle can be plotted on a triangular grid &lt;a href="http://www.mathrecreation.com/2016/01/the-triangle-of-triangles.html"&gt;triangle of triangles&lt;/a&gt;. Also, some puzzles, like the Towers of Hanoi (three pillars, constant number of disks) and the Three Jugs problem (three jugs, sharing a constant volume of liquid) &lt;a href="http://www.mathrecreation.com/2016/02/triangle-games-three-jugs-and-towers-of.html"&gt;can be displayed/solved&lt;/a&gt; with the help of a triangular grid.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
